# ============================================================
#  MINDSTATZ — Setup Guide & Environment Variables
#  Read this fully before deploying.
# ============================================================

# ── Step 1: Create a Supabase project ───────────────────────
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com → New Project
# 2. Choose a region close to your audience
# 3. Save your database password somewhere safe

# ── Step 2: Run the SQL setup ───────────────────────────────
# 1. In Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor → New Query
# 2. Paste the entire contents of supabase-setup.sql
# 3. Click Run — all tables, RLS policies, and triggers are created

# ── Step 3: Paste your credentials into the HTML files ──────
# Find these values at: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API

SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# In BOTH index.html AND admin.html, replace these two lines:
#   window.SUPABASE_URL  = 'https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co';
#   window.SUPABASE_ANON = 'YOUR_ANON_PUBLIC_KEY';
# with your actual values from above.

# ── Step 4: Generate your AES-256 secret key ────────────────
# This key encrypts all video URLs and metadata server-side.
# Generate a cryptographically random 32-byte hex string:
#
#   In your terminal:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#
#   Or online: https://generate.plus/en/bytes (32 bytes, hex output)
#
# Save this key — if you lose it, all encrypted video data
# becomes permanently unreadable.

MINDSTATZ_AES_KEY=your_64_character_hex_string_here

# ── Step 5: Deploy the Edge Function ────────────────────────
# The Edge Function decrypts video URLs server-side for members.
#
# Install Supabase CLI:
#   npm install -g supabase
#
# Link your project:
#   supabase login
#   supabase link --project-ref YOUR_PROJECT_REF
#
# Set your secrets (these live in Supabase, never in your repo):
#   supabase secrets set MINDSTATZ_AES_KEY=your_64_char_hex
#   supabase secrets set SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key
#     (Service role key: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API → service_role)
#
# Deploy the function:
#   supabase functions deploy get-video-url
#
# Verify it's live:
#   supabase functions list

# ── Step 6: Create your admin account ───────────────────────
# 1. Go to your live site (or localhost) and sign up normally
#    using the Sign In button → Create Account
# 2. Confirm your email (check inbox)
# 3. In Supabase Dashboard → Table Editor → profiles
#    Find your row and change role from 'member' to 'admin'
#    (or run this SQL):
#
#    UPDATE public.profiles
#    SET role = 'admin'
#    WHERE email = 'your-admin@email.com';
#
# 4. Sign in again — you'll be redirected to admin.html
# 5. Enter your password in the key unlock modal to activate
#    AES-256 decryption for the session

# ── Step 7: Configure CORS for your video CDN ───────────────
# If hosting videos on an external CDN (Cloudinary, Bunny, etc.),
# ensure CORS is set to allow your GitHub Pages domain:
#   Access-Control-Allow-Origin: https://yourusername.github.io

# ── Step 8: Push to GitHub Pages ────────────────────────────
# 1. Commit all files (supabase/ folder included)
# 2. Push to main branch
# 3. Settings → Pages → Deploy from main / root
# 4. Your site: https://yourusername.github.io/repo-name/

# ── Security Notes ──────────────────────────────────────────
# ✅ SUPABASE_ANON key is safe to expose in client-side code —
#    it only allows what RLS policies permit.
# ⛔ NEVER commit MINDSTATZ_AES_KEY or SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
#    to your repository. Use supabase secrets set only.
# ✅ The admin AES key is derived from password+UUID via PBKDF2
#    (310,000 iterations, SHA-256) — never stored anywhere.
# ✅ Video URLs are AES-256-GCM encrypted at rest in Postgres.
# ✅ Admin password is stored as SHA-256(password+UUID) hash.
# ✅ Access tokens stored as SHA-256(raw_token) — raw never saved.
# ✅ Row Level Security enforces access at the database level.
# ✅ The Edge Function verifies JWT before decrypting any URL.

# ── Encryption Flow Summary ─────────────────────────────────
#
#  ADMIN UPLOAD:
#    password + UUID ──PBKDF2──► AES-256 key (in memory only)
#    video URL ──AES-256-GCM──► encrypted blob ──► Postgres
#
#  MEMBER PLAYBACK:
#    Browser sends JWT ──► Edge Function
#    Edge Function verifies JWT + checks RLS
#    Edge Function decrypts URL with server secret
#    Plaintext URL returned over HTTPS ──► browser plays video
#
#  ADMIN PLAYBACK:
#    Admin enters password ──PBKDF2──► AES key (re-derived)
#    Encrypted blobs from DB ──AES-GCM decrypt──► plaintext
#    All decryption happens in-browser, key never leaves device
#
# ============================================================
